subMembers.name: Configuration
subMembers.description: This section describes the **ODataStore**'s configuration properties.

subMembers.name: beforeSend
subMembers.description: Specifies a function that customizes the request before it is sent to the server.

subMembers.name: deserializeDates
subMembers.description: Specifies whether the store serializes/parses date-time values.

subMembers.name: errorHandler
subMembers.description: Specifies a function that is executed when the **ODataStore** throws an error.

subMembers.name: fieldTypes
subMembers.description: Specifies the data field types. Accepts the following types: *"String"*, *"Int32"*, *"Int64"*, *"Boolean"*, *"Single"*, "*Decimal"* and *"[Guid]"*.

subMembers.name: filterToLower
subMembers.description: Specifies whether to convert string values to lowercase in filter and search requests. Applies to the following operations: *"startswith"*, *"endswith"*, *"contains"*, and *"notcontains"*.

subMembers.name: jsonp
subMembers.description: Specifies whether data should be sent using JSONP.

subMembers.name: keyType
subMembers.description: Specifies the type of the key property or properties.

subMembers.name: url
subMembers.description: Specifies the URL of an OData entity collection.

subMembers.name: withCredentials
subMembers.description: Specifies whether to send cookies, authorization headers, and client certificates in a cross-origin request.

properties.name: ODataStore
properties.description: The **ODataStore** is a store that provides an interface for loading and editing data from an individual OData entity collection and handling related events.

Methods.name: byKey(key_extraOptions)
Methods.description: Gets an entity with a specific key.

Methods.name: createQuery(loadOptions)
Methods.description: Creates a **Query** for the OData endpoint.
